properties.title: Response JSON Property/Variable Map
properties.description: A line by line mapping of JSON properties to variables.  Each line will take the form of JSON property name, followed by a "=>" delimiter, and then variable name.  Will be evaluated, so it may contain fields and variables.

properties.title: Request Method
properties.description: The REST method, like GET, PUT, POST, or DELETE

properties.title: Request Content
properties.description: The body of the request.  Will be evaluated, so it may contain fields and variables.

properties.title: Request Content Variable
properties.description: The variable holding the body of the request.

properties.title: Is a transaction sub process
properties.description: A flag that identifies whether this sub process is of type transaction.

properties.title: Request Content Type
properties.description: The content type of the request body, like application/json.  If no body is present, this is ignored.

properties.title: Response Content Type Variable
properties.description: The variable to hold the type of the body of the response, like application/json.

properties.title: Request Path
properties.description: The URL path of the service, typically starting with "/services".  Will be evaluated, so it may contain fields and variables.

properties.title: Response Content Variable
properties.description: The variable to hold the body of the response.
